Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract topics from psychiatric electronic health records (EHRs) in order to predict readmission risk for psychiatric patients. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of similarity metrics and data pipelines, which are common in the fields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses the identification of risk factor domains, which could potentially fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
